Class Enemy

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Thread

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Runnable, Collidable, Movable, org.jsfml.graphics.Drawable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    Boss

    public class Enemy
extends Character
implements Movable
    The Enemy class represents all enemies that can be spawned in the game. The values that are passed in dictate how this enemy will behave/look.

      • move

        public void move()
        Move this enemy closer to the player. This function works by first calculating whether or not the player is to the left of the right of this enemy and move the enemy in the relevant direction. Then the player is checked if they are above or below the enemy and the enemy moves in the correspoding direction
        Specified by:
        move in interface Movable
        See Also:

      • applyInteract

        public boolean applyInteract(Interactable interactClass)
        Applies an specific buff to this enemy. Interacts occur when an enemy has moved over some part of the environment. A boolean value is returned to prevent one interact buff being applied multiple times.
        Parameters:
        interactClass - (Interactable) The interactable to apply to the enemy
        Returns:
        (boolean) Whether or not the interact was applied.
